properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 16 at 9:56AM PST until February 17 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Spokane WA
properties.description:
...SNOWY CONDITIONS OVER THE MOUNTAIN PASSES THIS AFTERNOON AND
OVERNIGHT...

* WHAT...Mountain snow expected for areas south of Lake Chelan.
This includes Highway 2 near Stevens Pass to Coles Corners.
Total snow accumulations of 6 to 9 inches. Winds gusting as high
as 40 mph.

* WHERE...Stevens Pass.

* WHEN...Until 4 AM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery to slick road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow showers will increase in intensity
this afternoon and into the evening hours.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST MONDAY FOR AREAS SOUTH OF LAKE CHELAN ABOVE 3000 FEET
